---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const lastUpdated = 'May 11, 2026'
const legalName = 'VP Promos LLC'
const dba = 'Bighorn Threads'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Bighorn Threads"
  description="Privacy Policy for VP Promos LLC, doing business as Bighorn Threads — how we collect, use, share, and protect your information, including text-message (SMS) consent and your privacy rights."
  canonical="https://bighornthreads.com/legal/privacy-policy/"
>
  <section class="border-b border-hairline bg-paper pt-14 pb-12 sm:pt-16 sm:pb-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="kicker">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-heading text-4xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-charcoal sm:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-ash">
        {legalName} d/b/a {dba} &nbsp;·&nbsp; Las Vegas, Nevada &nbsp;·&nbsp; Last updated {lastUpdated}
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-concrete py-14 sm:py-20">
    <div class="legal mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>{legalName}</strong>, doing business as
        <strong>{dba}</strong> (&ldquo;Bighorn Threads,&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;),
        collects, uses, shares, and protects information about you when you visit
        <a href="https://bighornthreads.com">bighornthreads.com</a> (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;), request a quote,
        place an order, sign up at an event, or otherwise communicate with us. By using the Site or
        submitting information to us, you agree to this Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <h3>Information you give us</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contact and business details</strong> — name, company/organization, email address, phone number, and job site or shipping locations.</li>
        <li><strong>Project details</strong> — the products, decoration methods, quantities, sizes, artwork, logos, deadlines, and notes you share when requesting a quote or placing an order.</li>
        <li><strong>Communications</strong> — messages, emails, texts, and call notes when you contact us or we follow up with you.</li>
        <li><strong>Event opt-ins</strong> — information you provide at trade shows, expos, golf events, or similar through our QR-code or sign-up forms.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Usage and device data</strong> — IP address, browser type, device type, pages viewed, referring/exit pages, and timestamps.</li>
        <li><strong>Cookies and analytics</strong> — we use Google Analytics 4 and similar tools to understand how the Site is used. See &ldquo;Cookies &amp; Analytics&rdquo; below.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not knowingly collect Social Security numbers, government ID numbers, financial account numbers, or credit information through the Site.</p>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Prepare quotes, process and fulfill orders, and manage company stores;</li>
        <li>Communicate with you about your request, artwork proofs, production status, shipping, and invoicing;</li>
        <li>Provide customer service and respond to questions;</li>
        <li>Send appointment reminders and account/order notifications by email or text (with your consent where required);</li>
        <li>With your separate consent, send marketing messages about products, offers, and promotions by email or text;</li>
        <li>Operate, secure, maintain, and improve the Site and our services;</li>
        <li>Detect and prevent fraud, abuse, and spam; and</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations and enforce our agreements.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Text Messaging (SMS/MMS)</h2>
      <p>
        Bighorn Threads operates two separate, opt-in text-messaging programs. You may opt in to either,
        both, or neither by checking the corresponding consent box on a form at bighornthreads.com (for
        example, our contact / quote page or an event sign-up page), or by giving us your number with
        written consent at an in-person event:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Bighorn Threads Customer Care (non-marketing)</strong> — quote follow-ups, order and artwork-proof updates, production and delivery status, and appointment reminders. Estimated frequency: typically 2–6 messages per active order.</li>
        <li><strong>Bighorn Threads Promotions (marketing)</strong> — special offers, discounts, new products, and seasonal promotions. Estimated frequency: up to 4 messages per month.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Consent is not a condition of purchase. Consent to receive texts is not required to request a quote, place an order, or otherwise do business with us.
        <strong>Message and data rates may apply.</strong> Reply <strong>STOP</strong>, END, CANCEL,
        UNSUBSCRIBE, or QUIT to any message to unsubscribe from that program; reply <strong>HELP</strong>
        or INFO for assistance; or contact us at <a href="tel:+17029048923">(702) 904-8923</a> or
        <a href="mailto:info@bighornthreads.com">info@bighornthreads.com</a>. After you opt out we will
        send one confirmation message and then stop sending texts from that program. Carriers are not
        liable for delayed or undelivered messages. The full text-message program terms are described in
        our <a href="/legal/terms/">Terms &amp; Conditions</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>No mobile information will be shared with third parties or affiliates for marketing or
        promotional purposes. Information sharing with subcontractors in support services, such as
        customer service, is permitted. All other use case categories exclude text-messaging
        originator opt-in data and consent; this information will not be shared with any third
        parties.</strong>
      </p>

      <h2>4. Email Communications</h2>
      <p>
        We send transactional emails (quotes, proofs, order updates, invoices) as part of doing business
        with you. If you opt in, we may also send occasional marketing emails. Every marketing email
        includes an unsubscribe link; you can also email <a href="mailto:info@bighornthreads.com">info@bighornthreads.com</a> to opt out.
        Opting out of marketing email does not stop transactional messages about an active order.
      </p>

      <h2>5. How We Share Information</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal information. We share it only as follows:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Service providers / subcontractors</strong> — companies that help us operate, such as our CRM and messaging provider (HighLevel / LeadConnector), website hosting and security (Cloudflare), analytics (Google), product-data and supplier partners (e.g., SAGE and apparel suppliers/decorators), payment processors, and shipping carriers. These providers may use the information only to perform services for us.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal and safety</strong> — when required by law, subpoena, or legal process, or to protect the rights, property, or safety of Bighorn Threads, our customers, or others.</li>
        <li><strong>Business transfers</strong> — in connection with a merger, acquisition, financing, or sale of all or part of our business; any successor will be bound by this Policy.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We never sell, rent, or share mobile phone numbers or SMS opt-in data with third parties or affiliates for their own marketing.</p>

      <h2>6. Cookies &amp; Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        The Site uses cookies and similar technologies for basic functionality and to measure traffic and
        performance, primarily through Google Analytics 4. You can control cookies through your browser
        settings; disabling them may affect some features. You can opt out of Google Analytics via the
        <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.
        We honor Global Privacy Control (GPC) signals where applicable.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We keep personal information for as long as needed to provide our services, maintain business and
        accounting records, resolve disputes, and comply with legal obligations. We keep records of SMS
        and email consent (including the date, the form used, and the consent language shown) for as long
        as you are opted in and for a reasonable period afterward to document compliance.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect personal
        information. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee
        absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live (including under the Nevada privacy law, NRS Chapter 603A, and the
        California Consumer Privacy Act / CPRA), you may have the right to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Request access to the personal information we hold about you and how we use and share it;</li>
        <li>Request correction or deletion of your personal information;</li>
        <li>Opt out of the &ldquo;sale&rdquo; or &ldquo;sharing&rdquo; of your personal information — note that we do not sell or share personal information as those terms are commonly defined; and</li>
        <li>Not receive discriminatory treatment for exercising your rights.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To make a request, email <a href="mailto:info@bighornthreads.com">info@bighornthreads.com</a> or
        call <a href="tel:+17029048923">(702) 904-8923</a>. We may need to verify your identity before
        acting on a request. You may use an authorized agent where the law allows.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Children&rsquo;s Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is intended for businesses and adults. We do not knowingly collect personal information
        from children under 16. If you believe a child has provided us information, contact us and we will
        delete it.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>
        The Site may link to third-party websites and services (for example, supplier catalogs or social
        media). We are not responsible for their privacy practices; review their policies separately.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Policy from time to time. The &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date above reflects the
        most recent change. Material changes will be posted on this page; your continued use of the Site
        after changes take effect means you accept the updated Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>{legalName}</strong> d/b/a <strong>{dba}</strong><br />
        Las Vegas, Nevada, USA<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:info@bighornthreads.com">info@bighornthreads.com</a><br />
        Phone: <a href="tel:+17029048923">(702) 904-8923</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    color: var(--color-ash);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  .legal > p { margin-top: 1.15rem; }
  .legal > p:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .legal h2 {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-hairline);
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
  }
  .legal h3 {
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    color: var(--color-gold-700);
  }
  .legal ul {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.35rem;
    list-style: disc;
  }
  .legal ul li { margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  .legal ul li::marker { color: var(--color-gold-500); }
  .legal strong { color: var(--color-charcoal); font-weight: 600; }
  .legal a {
    color: var(--color-gold-700);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }
  .legal a:hover { color: var(--color-gold-600); }
  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .legal { font-size: 1.0625rem; }
    .legal h2 { font-size: 2rem; }
  }
</style>
